OL,3,CStuart Hall was given infected blood
OL,4,Cwhen being treated for leukaemia in
OL,5,C1984
OL,7,FStuart said: "People would say to me:
OL,8,F'are you going to sue?' But why would
OL,9,FI sue the hospital when they were
OL,10,Flooking after me and treating me for a
OL,11,Flife threatening illness? At that
OL,12,Fpoint, I was totally unaware of the
OL,13,Fknowledge that the government and the
OL,14,Fmedical profession had that there was
OL,15,Fpotentially a high risk of blood
OL,16,Fdonations having the virus within it.
OL,17,F"It makes me extremely angry. When you
OL,18,Fthink that how much it's affected my
OL,19,Flife over the last almost 30 years.
OL,20,FIt's just ridiculous. It's absolutely
OL,21,Fscandalous.J"I hope the government
OL,22,Fwill issue a formal apology to
OL,23,Feveryone. I hope they will get on and
OL,24,Ffinally, deal with the compensation. I
OL,25,Fthink they are dragging their heels. I
OL,26,Fthink they were trying to kick the can
